race.comment: TIERRA (7) brings winning Victorian form, albeit in lesser grade. But she's a progressive type who meets horses that have largely found their mark. She can use her early speed to overcome the wide draw and, if she can save something for the finish, she'll be hard to beat. THE MANSMAN (2) has been back to the trials since his last start. He keeps racing well and looks a lock for a top-three spot again, although he struggles to win. LOMAX (4) is another that needs all the favours but he's got the ability to be in the finish. KING OF WESSEX (3) is a last start winner that will bring confidence and can run well from a low draw, while ZAIN PRINCE (8) is worth some thought for quaddies and wider plays.
